cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SE, cs.NE 

This paper focuses on applying artificial neural networks for intrusion detection using system call data. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses different options for preprocessing system call data, which involves machine learning techniques such as word2vec and GloVe, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely categories as well. Additionally, the paper discusses the importance of not losing relevant information during preprocessing, which relates to software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper uses neural networks for classification, which falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE).
